|m}}, {{t+|it|istruttrice|f}}, {{t+|it|coach|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|コーチ|tr=kōchi}}, {{t+|ja|トレーナー|tr=torēnā}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|бапкер}}, {{t|kk|жаттықтырушы}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|គ្រូបង្វឹក}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|코치}}, {{t|ko|트레이너}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|rahêner|m|f}}, {{t+|kmr|antrenor|m|f}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|тренер}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|exercitor|m}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|treneris|m}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|treneris|m}}, {{t|lt|trenerė|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|тренер|m}}, {{t|mk|тренерка|f}}\n* Malay: {{t|ms|koc}}, {{t+|ms|jurulatih}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|mn|сургагч}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|trener|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|trenar|m}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t+|fa-ira|مُرَبّی}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|trener|m}}, {{t+|pl|trenerka|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|treinador|m}}, {{t|pt|treinadora|f}}, {{t+|pt|técnico|m}}, {{t+|pt|técnica|f}}, {{t+|pt|coach|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|antrenor|m}}, {{t+|ro|antrenoare|f}}, {{t+|ro|coach|m}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|тре́нер|m}} {{qualifier|male or female}}, {{t+|ru|тре́нерша|f}} {{qualifier|the female form is colloquial}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|тре́нер|m}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|tréner|m}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|tréner|m}}, {{t|sk|trénerka|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|trener|m}}, {{t|sl|trenerka|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|entrenador|m}}, {{t+|es|entrenadora|f}}, {{t+|es|míster|m}}, {{t|es|preparador|m}}, {{t|es|''coach''|m|f}}, {{t+|es|couch|c}} {{qualifier|United States}}, {{t+|es|técnico|m}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|mkufunzi}}, {{t+|sw|kocha}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|tränare|c}}, {{t+|sv|coach|c}}\n* Tajik: {{t|tg|тренер}}, {{t|tg|мураббӣ}}\n* Thai: {{t|th|ครูฝึก}}, {{t+|th|โค้ช}}, {{t|th|ผู้สอน}}, {{t|th|ผู้ฝึกสอน}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|koç}}, {{t+|tr|antrenör}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|trener}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|тре́нер|m}}, {{t|uk|тре́нерка|f}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|ٹْرینَر|m}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|trener}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|huấn luyện viên}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|etrinneu|m}}, {{t|wa|etrinnresse|f}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|long-distance bus}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|حافلة السفر|f|tr=ḥāfila al-safar}}, {{t|ar|حافلة النقل الخارجي|f|tr=ḥāfila al-naql al-khārijī}}, {{t|ar|حافلة النقل المدني|f|tr=ḥāfila al-naql al-madanī}}, {{t|ar|حَافِلَة الْمَسَافَات الْبَعِيدَة|f|tr=ḥāfilat al-masāfāt al-baʕīda}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|karr-boutin|m}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|autocar|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|長途巴士|tr=coeng4 tou4 baa1 si6-2}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|長途汽車|tr=chángtú qìchē}}, {{t+|cmn|客車|tr=kèchē}}\n*: Wu: {{t|wuu|客车}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|rutebil|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|touringcar|c}}, {{t+|nl|reisbus|m}}, {{t+|nl|snelbus|m}} {{qualifier|public transport}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|aŭtoĉaro}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|bussi}}, {{t+|fi|linja-auto}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|autocar|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Reisebus|m}}, {{t+|de|Überlandbus|m}}, {{t+|de|Bus|m}}\n* Greek: {{t|el|υπεραστικό λεωφορείο|n}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|távolsági autóbusz}}, {{t|hu|távolsági busz}}\n* Indonesian: {{t|id|bus jarak jauh}}, {{t|id|bus besar}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|bus|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|corriera|f}}, {{t+|it|pullman}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|高速バス}}, {{t+|ja|コーチ}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|otobûs|f}}\n* Malay: {{t|ms|koc}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|turbuss|m}}, {{t|nb|langdistansebuss|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|turbuss|m}}, {{t|nn|langdistansebuss|m}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|autokar}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|carreira|f}}, {{t+|pt|autocarro|m}}, {{t+|pt|ônibus|m}}, {{t|pt|autopullman|m}}, {{t|pt|autocarro de turismo}}, {{t|pt|ônibus rodoviario|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|autocar|n}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|авто́бус|m}}, {{t|ru|автобус дальнего следования|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|autocar|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|buss}}, {{t+|sv|långfärdsbuss}}\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|கோச்}}\n* Thai: {{t|th|รถโค้ช}}\n* Turkish: {{t|tr|şehirlerarası otobüs|s}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|авто́бус|m}}, {{t|uk|автобус далекого прямування|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|xe khách}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Slovak: {{t-check|sk|koč}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|intransitive|sports}} To [[train]].\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[instruct]]; to [[train]].\n#: {{ux|en|She has '''coached''' many opera stars.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To study under a tutor.\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To travel in a coach (sometimes ''coach it'').\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1653|author={{w|Edward Waterhouse (FRS)|Edward Waterhouse}}|title=A humble Apologie for Learning and Learned Men\n|passage=Affecting genteel fashions, '''coaching''' it to all quarters}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To convey in a coach.\n#* {{RQ:Pope Dunciad\n|passage=The needy poet sticks to all he meets, <br>'''Coached''', carted, trod upon, now loose, now fast. <br>And carried off in some dog's tail at last}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|outcoach|overcoach|recoach|uncoach|coachable}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|nl|bor=1|coachen}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|sports: train}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|тренирам}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|trénovat}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|coachen}}, {{t+|nl|trainen}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|valmentaa}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|entraîner}}, {{t+|fr|entrainer}}, {{t+|fr|coacher}}\n* German: {{t+|de|trainieren}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|προπονώ}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|אימן|tr=imén}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|edz}}, {{t+|hu|treníroz}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|allenare}}, {{t+|it|addestrare}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|rahênan}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|трени́ра}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|trenować|impf}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|treinar}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|antrena}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|trénovať}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|trenirati}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|entrenar}}, {{t+|es|cochear}} {{qualifier|Latin America}}, {{t|es|cochar}} {{qualifier|Central America}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|träna}}, {{t+|sv|coacha}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|instruct}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|opleiden}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|instruire}}\n* German: {{t+|de|ausbilden}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|oktat}}, {{t+|hu|képez}}, {{t+|hu|tanít}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|rahênan}}, {{t+|kmr|fêr kirin}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|трени́ра}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|instrui}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Adverb===\n{{en-adv|-}}\n\n# {{lb|en|chiefly|US}} Via the part of a commercial passenger airplane or train reserved for those paying the lower standard [[fare]]s; via the economy section.\n#: {{ux|en|John flew '''coach''' to Vienna, but first-class back home.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|en|coachability}}\n\n====References====\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=accho|Cacho|Chaco|chaco}}\n\n{{cln|en|terms derived from toponyms|terms of address}}\n{{C|en|Occupations|People|Carriages}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|nl|en|frm|de|hu}}\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|en|coach}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/koːtʃ/}}\n* {{IPA|nl|[koːtʃ]|a=BE}}\n* {{IPA|nl|[koʊ̯tʃ]|a=NL}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-coach.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|coach}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|m|-es,-en|+}}\n\n# [[trainer]], instructor, [[tutor]], {{l|en|coach}}\n# [[counselor]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|nl|bondscoach}}\n* {{l|nl|coachen}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|nl|koets}}\n\n{{C|nl|Occupations}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|en:coach}}\n{{bor+|fr|en|coach}}. {{doublet|fr|coche}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|cauvtch}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-coach.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Bananax47-coach.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Agen>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|coach}}, [[trainer]], [[instructor]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|fr|coacher}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|fr|cocha}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|it|en|frm|de|hu}}\n{{ubor|it|en|coach}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|có[tʃ],cò[tʃ]<r:DiPI>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m|#}}\n\n# {{l|en|coach}} (sports instructor)\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:[[+ (osoba)|+]]}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|pl|en|coach}}, from {{der|pl|frm|coche}}, from {{der|pl|de|Kutsche}}, from {{der|pl|hu|kocsi}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|kołcz|a=LL-Q809 (pol)-Olaf-coach.wav|h=coach}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-pr}}\n\n# {{lb|pl|sports}} {{l|en|coach}}, [[trainer]] {{gl|person who trains another}}\n# {{lb|pl|psychology}} {{l|en|coach}}, [[instructor]]\n#: {{syn|pl|szkoleniowiec|trener}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-decl-noun-m-pr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-in}}\n\n# [[coachwork]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-decl-noun-m-in|nomp=coache}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|pl|title=adjective|coachingowy}}\n{{col|pl|title=noun|coaching}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n\n{{C|pl|Male people|Occupations}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|pt|en|frm|de|hu}}\n{{unadapted borrowing|pt|en|coach}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|côutchi^^}}\n* {{rhymes|pt|owtʃi|otʃi|otʃ|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|mfbysense|coaches}}\n\n# motivational [[speaker]]\n# [[life coach]] {{gloss|professional who helps clients to achieve their personal goals}}\n\n{{C|pt|People}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|es|en|frm|de|hu}}\n{{ubor|es|en|coach}}. {{doublet|es|coche}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|couch|hyph=coach}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|es|sport}} {{l|en|coach}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{es-unadapted}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n* {{R:es:DAMER}}\n* [https://www.anle.us/noticias/publicaciones/diccionario-de-anglicismos-del-espanol-estadounidense/ Diccionario de anglicismos del español estadounidense]\n\n==Swedish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|sv|en|frm|de|hu}}\n{{bor+|sv|en|coach}}. {{etydate|1962}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# {{l|en|coach}}; a trainer or instructor\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-infl-noun-c-er}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:svenska.se}}"}}